  "prompt": "Which is the best Hindi movie ever made?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" Hindi movie ever made is highly subjective and varies widely based on personal preferences, criteria, and the specific aspects one considers most important (such as storytelling, acting, direction, music, cultural impact, etc.). However, some Hindi films are frequently cited by critics, audiences, and film experts as among the best ever made:\n\n1. **Sholay (1975)** - Directed by Ramesh Sippy, this epic action-adventure film is often regarded as a quintessential Bollywood movie, showcasing exemplary performances from its cast and bringing several iconic characters to life.\n   \n2. **Mother India (1957)** - Directed by Mehboob Khan, this film is a landmark in Indian cinema, illustrating the struggles of a rural Indian woman and her family. It was the first Indian film to be nominated for an Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film.\n   \n3. **Mughal-E-Azam (1960)** - Directed by K. Asif, this epic historical drama is renowned for its grandeur, lavish sets, and powerful performances, particularly by Prithviraj Kapoor and Madhubala.\n   \n4. **Lagaan (2001)** - Directed by Ashutosh Gowariker, the film presents an extraordinary story set during the British Raj, combining sports drama with historical elements. It also received an Academy Award nomination for Best Foreign Language Film.\n   \n5. **Pather Panchali (1955)** - Although technically a Bengali film, directed by Satyajit Ray, it is often included in discussions of great Indian cinema and is celebrated for its storytelling and realistic portrayal of rural life.\n\nOthers often mentioned include **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)**, **Guide (1965)**, **Dangal (2016)**, and **3 Idiots (2009)**.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" movie can differ greatly depending on who you ask.",
